We then used our kinematic outcome measures to calculate margin of stability (MoS) using previously described methods [10, 33]. Specifically, we defined MoS as the difference in position between the lateral base of support (BoS) and the extrapolated center of mass (XCoM) as follows:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
